**Feature Suggestion**
// Spot/perp future arb strategy
// Stop bot placing one side of arbitrage if assets are not available to place the other side of the arbitrage.
// Warn: User should still be able to buy/sell using leverage if desired.

**Impact**
// This will protect users from exposure to "one sided" trades where assets are not available. Also, users will not be forced to hold assets they may not want on their balance sheets to mitigate this risk.

**Additional context**
The purpose of this strategy is to make a profit placing opposing trades on different exchanges/markets. The current functionality for this strategy allows for the bot to place a trade on one exchange even if the required assets are not present/available to trade with in the opposing market. To mitigate this, the user must hold the opposing asset just in case the arbitrage bot attempts to place trades in the opposite position than what would be expected. 

eg. 
- Arbitrage BTC/USDT spot market against BTC/USDT Perpetual Futures market. 
If I want to hold USDT and trade in/out of BTC, and expect the arbitrage bot to place a BTC short on the futures market, and go long on the BTC spot market, then I am fine holding USDT only. However if the arbitrage percentages move the other way then the bot will place a BTC long position in the futures but fail to place a short/sell position in the BTC spot market as I do not hold and BTC.
- Therefore exposing me to an unknown outcome on the futures market, or forcing me to hold BTC in the spot market to account for this scenario


It would also be great if we could set multiple arbitrage percentage levels to have multiple positions open in the same market/pair :)

